    <thetext>Created attachment 1182416
s390 support

Description of problem:

There doesn&apos;t seem to be a good reason to avoid building on s390, and
lack of the package apparently requires all MPI packages to have messy conditionals for openmpi.  It may or may not actually be useful, but I don&apos;t
understand the previous comment about not having suitable hardware --
presumably you can use shared memory, at least.

The attached patch allows it to build (on f23, f24, rawhide) so that other
packages don&apos;t need the special case.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
1.10.3-2</thetext>
